  • public class TryNode
extends ExceptionHandlingNode
    ExceptionHandlingNode extension that represents the declaration of a try node type. See decodeStatement(TreeNode, String, Location, boolean, boolean) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • decodeStatement

        public static TryNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                      java.lang.String statement,
                      Location location,
                      boolean require,
                      boolean scope)
        Decode the given statement into a TryNode instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.
        The only correct input is "try"
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a TryNode instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        scope - Whether or not the given statement is the beginning of a scope.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a TryNode.
